library(tidyverse)
library(magrittr)
library(brms)

options(brms.backend = "cmdstanr", mc.cores = 4)
df = read_csv("http://www.stat.columbia.edu/~gelman/arm/examples/radon/srrs2.dat")
## Rows: 12777 Columns: 25
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (11): state, state2, zip, basement, rep, wave, starttm, stoptm, startdt, stopdt, county
## dbl (13): idnum, stfips, region, typebldg, floor, room, stratum, activity, pcterr, adjwt, dupflag, zipflag, cntyfips
## lgl  (1): windoor
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
radon = df %>%
    filter(state == "MN") %>%
    mutate(log.radon = log(ifelse(activity==0, .1, activity))) %>%
select(log.radon, floor, county)
